summary:
Mutation of the ARTEMIS gene leads to severe combined immunodeficiency (SCID), specifically classified under autosomal recessive forms characterized by profound deficiencies in both T and B lymphocytes. This is supported clinically by inclusion of Artemis-related cases among standard indications for hematopoietic stem cell transplant therapy used across major medical references. 

\boxed{YES}

The summary focuses only on direct clinical relevance regarding whether ARTEMIS mutations lead to SCID—without including non-clinical or speculative details—and clearly aligns with established diagnostic criteria from trusted health resources such as those cited above. The conclusion reflects current consensus based upon documented patient outcomes and therapeutic interventions tied directly to immune dysfunction patterns seen in known SCID subtypes.

